The Ibadan Field Office of the Department of Petroleum Resources (DPR) has restated its commitment to check the hoarding and diversion of petroleum products. Mr Oluyemi Olaonipekun, Controller Operations, DPR Ibadan Field Office, told newsmen in Ibadan on Monday that the office would continue to intensify its surveillance on illegal petroleum activities. Olaonipekun said that DPR recently sealed five petrol stations suspected to be hoarding the Purified Motor Spirit (PMS). “ We noticed that there ought not be scarcity, especially with quantity of products being pushed out, so we intensified surveillance. “We suspected that the stations were hoarding products, they refused to sell, and refused our efforts to dip into their tanks,” he said. Olaonipekun stated that DPR would ensure that petroleum products distributed to stations were sold to members of the public. “Apart from ensuring that hoarding does not work, we shall ensure that sharp practices such as pump adjustment is stamped out,” he said.(NAN) Currently in Social Media platform of NTA, Largest TV in Africa. Iam a graduate of Mass Communication with special interest on social media and Online Editor and a Reporter.